    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "M. c. Hunter, real estate broker,\ntoday made the city written offer\nof $4,000 net cash for the ground\nnear the city crematory that is\nsought by the Inland Empire rail.\nway. 1t is presumed that Mr.\nHunter is acting for the railway\nbut his communication does not\nstate this.\n\n\nThe land wanted is approxim\nately 400 feet in length by 200 in\nwidth and embraces the bulk of\nblock II, in Second addition to\nRailroad addition. Half of the land\nis in the river bed under water,\nwhile the other half sets well above\nthe river on good grade."
    }
